### Keyboard Events — `KeyEvent.h`

#### `KeyEvent` (abstract intermediate base)
```cpp
class PIGEON_API KeyEvent
    : public EventClassCategory<EventCategoryKeyboard | EventCategoryInput>
{
public:
    int GetKeyCode() const;
protected:
    KeyEvent(int keycode);
    int m_KeyCode;
};
```
Does **not** inherit `EventClassType` — it is not dispatchable by itself.

#### `KeyPressedEvent`
```cpp
class PIGEON_API KeyPressedEvent : public KeyEvent, public EventClassType<EventType::KeyPressed>
{
public:
    KeyPressedEvent(int keycode, int repeatCount);
    int GetRepeatCount() const;
    std::string ToString() const override; // "KeyPressedEvent: <code> (<n> repeats)"
};
```
`repeatCount` is 0 for the initial press, 1 for any OS-generated key-repeat (Win32 `lParam` bit 30).

#### `KeyReleasedEvent`
```cpp
class PIGEON_API KeyReleasedEvent : public KeyEvent, public EventClassType<EventType::KeyReleased>
{
public:
    KeyReleasedEvent(int keycode);
    std::string ToString() const override;
};
```

#### `KeyTypedEvent`
```cpp
class PIGEON_API KeyTypedEvent : public KeyEvent, public EventClassType<EventType::KeyTyped>
{
public:
    KeyTypedEvent(int keycode);
    std::string ToString() const override;
};
```
Sourced from `WM_CHAR`. The keycode is the **character value** (Unicode code point), not a virtual-key code.

