### Mouse Events — `MouseEvent.h`

#### `MouseMovedEvent`
```cpp
class PIGEON_API MouseMovedEvent
    : public EventClassCategory<EventCategoryMouse | EventCategoryInput>
    , public EventClassType<EventType::MouseMoved>
{
public:
    MouseMovedEvent(float x, float y);
    float GetX() const;
    float GetY() const;
    std::string ToString() const override;
};
```
Coordinates are client-area pixel positions (from `LOWORD`/`HIWORD` of `lParam`).

#### `MouseScrolledEvent`
```cpp
class PIGEON_API MouseScrolledEvent
    : public EventClassCategory<EventCategoryMouse | EventCategoryInput>
    , public EventClassType<EventType::MouseScrolled>
{
public:
    MouseScrolledEvent(float xOffset, float yOffset);
    float GetXOffset() const;
    float GetYOffset() const;
    std::string ToString() const override;
};
```
`yOffset` is normalised to wheel-delta units (divided by `WHEEL_DELTA = 120`). `xOffset` is always 0 because `WM_MOUSEWHEEL` carries no horizontal component.

#### `MouseButtonEvent` (abstract intermediate base)
```cpp
class PIGEON_API MouseButtonEvent
    : public EventClassCategory<EventCategoryMouse | EventCategoryInput | EventCategoryMouseButton>
{
public:
    int GetMouseButton() const;
protected:
    MouseButtonEvent(int button);
    int m_Button;
};
```

#### `MouseButtonPressedEvent`
```cpp
class PIGEON_API MouseButtonPressedEvent
    : public MouseButtonEvent
    , public EventClassType<EventType::MouseButtonPressed>
{
public:
    MouseButtonPressedEvent(int button);
    std::string ToString() const override;
};
```

#### `MouseButtonReleasedEvent`
```cpp
class PIGEON_API MouseButtonReleasedEvent
    : public MouseButtonEvent
    , public EventClassType<EventType::MouseButtonReleased>
{
public:
    MouseButtonReleasedEvent(int button);
    std::string ToString() const override;
};
```

Mouse button codes (`WIN_PG_MOUSE_BUTTON_LEFT` etc.) are platform constants defined in `Platform/Windows/WindowsInputKeyCodeMapping.h` and are translated through `PlatformInput::GetMouseButtonCode` before being stored in the ECS.

