## `BindEventFn` Helper

Defined in `Core.h`:

```cpp
template <auto EventFn, typename EventHandler>
auto BindEventFn(EventHandler* handler);
```

Returns a lambda that captures `handler` and invokes `EventFn` on it with forwarded arguments. Used as:

```cpp
m_Data.m_Window->SetEventCallback(pg::BindEventFn<&Application::OnEvent, Application>(this));
```

This is the mechanism by which the platform window's `EventCallbackFn` (`std::function<void(Event&)>`) is bound to `Application::OnEvent`.

