## Event Flow: Platform to ECS

The complete pipeline from OS message to ECS-readable data is:

```
Win32 WM_* message
    └── WindowsWindow::WindowProc
            └── WindowsWindow::ProcessEvent  (switch on msg)
                    └── Constructs pg::Event subclass on the stack
                            └── calls m_Data.EventCallback(event)   [= Application::OnEvent]
                                    ├── Direct handling:
                                    │       OnWindowClose  -> sets m_Running = false
                                    │       OnWindowResize -> calls Renderer::OnWindowResize,
                                    │                         sets m_Minimized flag
                                    └── ECS bridge (if not minimized):
                                            World::EmplaceExternalEvent<XxxEventComponent>(...)
                                                    └── Creates entt entity, attaches
                                                        EventComponent + XxxEventComponent
                                                        (deferred, flushed after Update())
```

`EmplaceExternalEvent` (on `World`) is the only way external (non-system) code injects event entities. It creates a new entity immediately but queues the component attachment as a deferred request so systems never see a partially-initialised entity.

Every event entity also receives `pg::EventComponent` (a trivial tag struct with a single `bool m_Dummy` field). `World::ClearEvents` uses this tag at the end of each `Update()` to destroy all event entities in a single registry view sweep.

---

## Layer Stack and Event Propagation

`Application` owns a `LayerStack` (a `std::vector<S_Ptr<Layer>>`). The `Layer` base class declares:

```cpp
virtual bool OnEvent(const Event& event) { return false; }
```

**Important**: `Application::OnEvent` does **not** iterate the layer stack. It processes events itself (window bookkeeping + ECS bridging) and returns. The `Layer::OnEvent` virtual exists in the interface but is never called by `Application` in the current implementation. Layers receive `OnUpdate` and `OnRender` each frame — not individual event callbacks. Event data reaches layers indirectly through the ECS (`InputStateSingletonComponent`, `UIOnClickOneFrameComponent`, etc.).

`ImGuiLayer` (the only non-test overlay) similarly does not override `OnEvent`; ImGui input is captured at the Win32 level via the forwarded `ImGui_ImplWin32_WndProcHandler` call inside `WindowProc`, before the engine's own event processing.

---

## ECS Event Components

These structs live in `Pigeon/Core/` and are the ECS-side equivalents of the platform event objects. They carry no inheritance hierarchy — each is a plain aggregate.

| Component | Fields | Source event |
|---|---|---|
| `KeyPressedEventComponent` | `int m_KeyCode` | `KeyPressedEvent` |
| `KeyReleasedEventComponent` | `int m_KeyCode` | `KeyReleasedEvent` |
| `KeyTypedEventComponent` | `int m_KeyCode` | `KeyTypedEvent` |
| `MouseMovedEventComponent` | `float m_MouseX`, `float m_MouseY` | `MouseMovedEvent` |
| `MouseScrolledEventComponent` | `float m_XOffset`, `float m_YOffset` | `MouseScrolledEvent` |
| `MouseButtonPressedEventComponent` | `int m_Button` | `MouseButtonPressedEvent` |
| `MouseButtonReleasedEventComponent` | `int m_Button` | `MouseButtonReleasedEvent` |
| `WindowResizeEventComponent` | `unsigned int m_Width`, `unsigned int m_Height` | `WindowResizeEvent` |
| `WindowCloseEventComponent` | `bool m_Dummy` | `WindowCloseEvent` |
| `EventComponent` | `bool m_Dummy` | Tag — present on every event entity |

`KeyCode` values are passed through `PlatformInput::GetKeyCode` / `GetMouseButtonCode` before being stored, so systems always see platform-independent key codes (defined in `KeyCodes.h`).

`repeatCount` from `KeyPressedEvent` is **not** bridged into `KeyPressedEventComponent`. Systems do not receive the repeat count.

---

## Event Lifetime

```
Application::OnEvent                         (synchronous, on OS thread)
    -> World::EmplaceExternalEvent           (creates entity, queues deferred attach)
World::Update()
    -> FlushDeferredRequests()               (attaches EventComponent + XxxEventComponent)
    -> Systems run (read event views)
    -> ClearEvents()                         (destroys all entities with EventComponent)
```

Event entities are **single-frame**: created during or before `Update()`, readable by all systems that run in that same `Update()`, and destroyed before the next frame begins.

---

## Key Systems That Consume Event Components

| System | Event components read |
|---|---|
| `InputSystem` | All 7 input event component types; writes `InputStateSingletonComponent` |
| `CameraSystem` | `KeyPressedEventComponent`, `MouseScrolledEventComponent`, `WindowResizeEventComponent`; writes `OrthographicCameraComponent` |
| `UIEventSystem` | Does not read event components directly — reads `InputStateSingletonComponent` (post-`InputSystem`) |

