## Testing Infrastructure

The `Testing` platform provides `TestingWindow::TESTING_TriggerEvent(pg::Event*)`, which calls the registered `EventCallback` directly. Unit tests use this to inject events without a Win32 message loop.

Tests in `UT_Core/InputSystemTest.cpp` and `UT_Core/CameraSystemTest.cpp` bypass the platform layer entirely: they write `XxxEventComponent` structs directly into the ECS registry with `GetRegistryDirect()` (a test-only accessor), then call `World::Update()`. This exercises system logic without involving `Application::OnEvent`.

